<br>
For main hand, the damage bonus at the lower levels is pretty insignificant.  It doesn't start to really have a large impact until 50+ and especially 60+.  I thought I recalled the bonus being floor((level-30)/3), which would put 33 as the first level with a bonus.  It might be ceil((level-27)/3), which would mean 28 would be the first.<br>
<br>
I really would not worry about these issue much pre-50.  I'd just get fast weapons of every type and use 'em to max out all my skills.  For the lowbie levels, you'll be leveling so quickly and upgrading your gear so often that it doesn't make sense to spend a lot of time optimizing your DPS and taunt.  Once you're 55+ and leveling starts to slow down a lot, that's when it makes sense to start thinking about gear a bit more. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nezmeron>Nezmeron</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 63<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/11/03 4:23:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=206.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Perfect!</span><hr size=1> Thank you, Bjond!  That's exactly what I was looking for, actually.  Basicly, if I don't have to worry about it for a while, then I won't.  <br>
